The invention relates to a method for synchronously playing a multi-computer video based on the refresh rate of a display card and belongs to the technical field of digital multimedia players. For improving the stability of a frame rate and synchronization effect in the process of playing the multi-computer video, the method provided by the invention comprises a step of presetting the display card and a step of synchronous playing of a node computer and control of the frame rate, wherein in the step of presetting the display card, a main control computer and the node computer set a refresh frequency of the display card according to the frame rate required by playing and simultaneously start a vertical synchronization function of the display card; and in the step of synchronous playing of the node computer and control of the frame rate, the node computer extracts video data from a video source data buffer and carries out multi-computer synchronous playing and frame rate control according to the preset refresh frequency of the display card. Through the technical scheme of the invention, multi-computer synchronization problem caused by abnormal network communication and abnormal network response is greatly reduced without increasing any hardware cost; multi-computer synchronization and the frame rate are controlled by using the refresh rate of the display card; and the stable playing frame rate and the optimal synchronization effect are realized.
